# Global Coding Standards

## Context

- Applies to all code and development activities
- Ensures consistent code quality and development practices
- Maintains project standards across all team members

## Critical Rules

- Write clean, readable, and maintainable code
- Use descriptive names for variables, functions, and components
- Follow DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principles
- Implement proper error handling and validation
- Write comprehensive documentation and comments
- Use consistent formatting and indentation
- Test all new functionality before deployment
- Follow security best practices and input validation
- Ensure accessibility compliance (WCAG guidelines)
- Optimize for performance and user experience

## Examples

<example>
  // ✅ DO: Write clean, readable code
  const calculateUserDiscount = (user: User, orderTotal: number): number => {
    if (!user.isActive) return 0;
    
    const baseDiscount = user.membershipLevel * 0.05;
    const totalDiscount = Math.min(baseDiscount * orderTotal, orderTotal * 0.25);
    
    return Math.round(totalDiscount * 100) / 100;
  };
</example>

